ce:section.ce:para:
In our study, our attempts to synthesize C-BN quantum dots by using only urea and boric acid in domestic microwaves were not successful. However, by adding trace amount of citric acid, stable colloidal C-BN quantum dots with bright fluorescence at aqueous phase were successfully synthesized (Fig. 1
                        ). In a typical synthesis of C-BN quantum dots, a modified microwave synthesis method, which was proposed by Bourlinos et al., was used [23]. Bourlinos et al. used 1 g citric acid, 1 g urea and 1 g boric acid to synthesize boron (B) doped graphene quantum dots in a domestic microwave [23]. In our study, the amount of citric acid was decreased by 1000 fold and C-BN quantum dots were synthesized in a domestic microwave by heating aqueous solution of boron, nitrogen and carbon precursors at 750 W for 5 min (Fig. 1). Elemental analysis on quantum dots which were synthesized with different Boric Acid : Urea : Citric acid mass ratio revealed that BCN quantum dots can also form besides C-BN quantum dots when different mass ratios of B, N and C precursors were used (Fig. 2
                        ). Our results indicated that microwave synthesis method can be a powerful tool for selective synthesis of BCN and C-BN ternary quantum dots just by tuning molar ratio of B, N and C precursor mass ratio (Fig. 2). To the best of our knowledge, this is the first study in which boron and nitrogen rich (with lesser amount of carbon) 2-D quantum dots are synthesized through a very simple bottom-up synthesis method within minutes.

Size and monodispersity of C-BN quantum dots were checked with TEM and DLS. The TEM images of C-BN and BCN quantum dots showed that C-BN and BCN quantum dots had 2−3 nm size with uniform size distribution (Fig. 3
                        , Fig. 4
                        ). Also, size histograms obtained by DLS showed that C-BN and BCN quantum dots had uniform size distribution between 1 nm – 3 nm with mean around 2 nm (Fig. 5
                        ). All of these results are consistent with sizes of other graphene and graphitic quantum dots synthesized in literature [14,79–82].
